500|$|Kennedy had no <b>illusions</b> <b>about</b> his studio's {{place in}} the realm of {{cinematic}} art. A journalist once complimented him on FBO's recent output: [...] "You have had some good pictures this year." [...] Kennedy jocularly inquired, [...] "What the hell were they?" [...] In her history of RKO, author Betty Lasky points to the pre-Kennedy Broken Laws (1924), directed by Roy William Neill and starring Dorothy Davenport (again billed as Mrs. Wallace Reid) as exemplifying the rare [...] "unforgettable picture of the higher caliber" [...] put out by FBO.|$|E
